DAAD奖提名陈述

被提名人：刘帅 (Liu Shuai)

刘帅目前在德国科隆媒体艺术学院攻读研究生学位，同时担任暨南大学人工智能与新媒体艺术研究中心研究员和中国人民大学数字人文研究院研究员，专注于人工智能与艺术交叉研究。

核心项目包括与英国伦敦金匠大学博士候选人Yiqing Tian合作的Ismism Machine项目，构建数据库驱动的AI系统探讨当代艺术生产模式。他创作的AI实时生成作品Prosomoíosi（2025）和Phantastikè（2024）运用TouchDesigner、StreamDiffusion等前沿技术。

学术合作方面，他与Mar Canet Sola共同工作并合著论文"From Code to Camera: The Making and Meaning of Prosomoíosi (Simulation), an AI Documentary Film"，探讨AI纪录片的制作与意义。此外，他与科隆媒体艺术学院、维也纳应用艺术大学合作推进LUDUS Magazine项目。

近期重要展览包括：2025年中国人民大学数字人文研究院"技术哲学文化学科"展览、德国科隆LUDUS Magazine项目、歌德学院"Solitude: Loneliness & Freedom"展、FIRST国际电影节西宁站；2024年德国鲁尔河畔剧院"Curiosity didn't kill the cat"展演；2023年波兰格但斯克SZTUKA NUMERYCZNA数字艺术节。

刘帅通过AI艺术研究、国际展览经历和跨文化学术合作，体现了DAAD奖倡导的学术交流精神，在连接东西方数字艺术传统方面展现研究潜力。

推荐意见：基于其学术研究态度和国际合作成就，推荐刘帅获得DAAD奖认可。

---

DAAD Prize Nomination Statement

Nominee: Liu Shuai

Liu Shuai is currently pursuing graduate studies at Academy of Media Arts Cologne while serving as researcher at both AI and New Media Art Research Center of Jinan University and Digital Humanities Research Center of Renmin University of China, focusing on AI-art intersection research.

Core projects include the Ismism Machine project collaborating with Yiqing Tian (PhD candidate, Goldsmiths, University of London), constructing database-driven AI systems exploring contemporary art production models. His AI real-time generation works Prosomoíosi (2025) and Phantastikè (2024) utilize cutting-edge technologies such as TouchDesigner and StreamDiffusion.

In academic collaboration, he has worked with Mar Canet Sola and co-authored the paper "From Code to Camera: The Making and Meaning of Prosomoíosi (Simulation), an AI Documentary Film," exploring the creation and significance of AI documentary films. Additionally, he collaborates with Academy of Media Arts Cologne and University of Applied Arts Vienna on the LUDUS Magazine project.

Recent major exhibitions include: 2025 "Technical Philosophy and Cultural Studies" exhibition at Digital Humanities Research Center, Renmin University of China; LUDUS Magazine project in Cologne, Germany; "Solitude: Loneliness & Freedom" at Goethe-Institut; FIRST International Film Festival Xining; 2024 "Curiosity didn't kill the cat" at Theatre an der Ruhr, Germany; 2023 SZTUKA NUMERYCZNA Digital Arts Festival, Gdansk, Poland.

Through AI art research, international exhibition experience, and cross-cultural academic collaboration, Liu Shuai embodies the academic exchange spirit advocated by the DAAD Prize, demonstrating research potential in connecting Eastern and Western digital art traditions.

Recommendation: Based on his academic research attitude and international collaboration achievements, Liu Shuai is recommended for DAAD Prize recognition.
